  }, "Including at least one song in your routine about the lesson topic of the day"), mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ul"
  }, "Varying your actions as you sing - hand movement songs, standing, sitting, marching, etc"), mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ul"
  }, "Saying the kids names (and they love name games every time)")), mdx("br", null), mdx("h4", null, "Avoid Resorting to Sugar"), mdx("p", null, "Some parents want to avoid having to resort to sugar to engage kids. My wife and I are such parents. Modern American sugar consumption is objectively an outlier and we\u2019re not benefiting from it. This is just something to be cognizant of. Between all the adults who run primary, it can pretty much be counted on for kids to be given fun dip, candy bars, brownies, etc on most weeks at least once. I have increasingly avoided contributing to that."), mdx("br", null), mdx("p", null, "If you're a chorister, hopefully this helps. Enjoy the experience. You have so much to learn and benefit from kids!"));
